text: Keet-McElhany House is a historic home located at Springfield, Greene County, Missouri. It was built in 1881, and enlarged in 1886, and remodeled in 1900. It is a two-story, brick dwelling with a frame attic and reflects Italianate and Queen Anne style design elements. It features a multi-hipped and gable roof, porch with a projecting gable, and round corner tower. (includes 13 photographs from 1983) It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1984. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Missouri Category:Italianate architecture in Missouri Category:Queen Anne architecture in Missouri Category:Houses completed in 1881 Category:Buildings and structures in Springfield, Missouri Category:National Register of Historic Places in Greene County, Missouri
